00:27:14.430 --> 00:27:19.870
OK, so you take derivative
over phi 1 corresponding to o1

00:27:19.870 --> 00:27:22.030
and then phi 2
corresponding to o2,

00:27:22.030 --> 00:27:27.410
et cetera, and the phi
n corresponding to xn.

00:27:27.410 --> 00:27:29.060
And then at the end
of the calculation,

00:27:29.060 --> 00:27:32.480
after you have done
the derivative,

00:27:32.480 --> 00:27:36.760
you set all the phi to 0, OK?

00:27:36.760 --> 00:27:43.700
So then you have extracted
n-point function, OK?

00:27:43.700 --> 00:27:45.550
So this is the same
that you expand

00:27:45.550 --> 00:27:49.750
that exponential in power series
and then only extract terms

00:27:49.750 --> 00:27:51.800
power n in phi, OK?

00:27:51.800 --> 00:27:54.110
So same thing.

00:27:54.110 --> 00:27:57.180
And now because this
is now equal to that--

00:27:57.180 --> 00:28:01.040
so we can write this in
terms of gravity quantities.

00:28:01.040 --> 00:28:04.120
So writing as n-point
function of SE

00:28:04.120 --> 00:28:17.790
will normalize SE as a function
phi c, now phi 1 x1, phi n xn.

00:28:17.790 --> 00:28:21.470
Then at the end, you
take phi equal to 0, OK?

00:28:21.470 --> 00:28:25.580
All the phi to 0, OK?

00:28:25.580 --> 00:28:31.900
So now you in principle, by
calculating the gravity action

00:28:31.900 --> 00:28:34.520
with the appropriate
boundary condition,

00:28:34.520 --> 00:28:39.104
then you would have obtained
any n-point functions

00:28:39.104 --> 00:28:40.020
from the field theory.

